Sentencas: The electrochemical characteristics of the solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) cathodes prepared by infiltration of (La0.85Sr0.15)(0.9)MnO3-delta (LSM) nanoparticles into porous Y0.5Bi1.5O3 (YSB) backbones are investigated in terms of overpotential, interfacial polarization resistance, and single cell performance obtained with three-electrode cell, symmetrical cell, and single cell, respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical characteristics of solid oxide fuel cell cathodes prepared by infiltrating (La,Sr)MnO3 nanoparticles into yttria-stabilized bismuth oxide backbones

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction confirms the formation of perovskite LSM by heating the infiltrated nitrates at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical characteristics of solid oxide fuel cell cathodes prepared by infiltrating (La,Sr)MnO3 nanoparticles into yttria-stabilized bismuth oxide backbones

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of the electrode measured using Van der Pauw method is 1.67 S cm(-1), which is acceptable at the typical SOFC operating temperatures.
Titulo: Electrochemical characteristics of solid oxide fuel cell cathodes prepared by infiltrating (La,Sr)MnO3 nanoparticles into yttria-stabilized bismuth oxide backbones

Sentencas: The single cell with the LSM infiltrated YSB cathode generates maximum power densities of 0.23, 0.45, 0.78, and 1.13W cm(-2) at 600, 650, 700, and 750 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical characteristics of solid oxide fuel cell cathodes prepared by infiltrating (La,Sr)MnO3 nanoparticles into yttria-stabilized bismuth oxide backbones

Sentencas: The oxygen reduction mechanism on the cathode is studied by analyzing the impedance spectra obtained under various temperatures and oxygen partial pressures.
Titulo: Electrochemical characteristics of solid oxide fuel cell cathodes prepared by infiltrating (La,Sr)MnO3 nanoparticles into yttria-stabilized bismuth oxide backbones

Sentencas: The impedance spectra under various cathodic current densities are also measured to study the effect of cathodic polarization on the performance of the cathode.
Titulo: Electrochemical characteristics of solid oxide fuel cell cathodes prepared by infiltrating (La,Sr)MnO3 nanoparticles into yttria-stabilized bismuth oxide backbones
